         <entryFree xml:id="k000225" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000225-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt" source="#biblk000225-1">pingbanfang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000225-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">平板枋</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000225-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">平板枋</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000225-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin" source="#biblk000225-1" type="ATTCAT_preferred">píngbǎnfāng</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000225-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">p'ing-pan-fang</term>
            <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000225</idno>
            <note type="Note">
               <p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000225-2">Pingbanfang is a tie beam with a rectilinear section that is placed on top of the pillar top tie beam (<term ref="/keyword/k000115">e’fang 額枋</term>) to support <term ref="/keyword/k000019">dougong 斗栱</term> (Liang 1981, 77). The term pingbanfang is equivalent to the <term type="dynasty" ref="/keyword/k000074">Song dynasty</term> term <term ref="/keyword/k000218">pupaifang</term> and is most commonly found in the <title ref="https://tinyurl.com/bd6byucb">Gongcheng zuofa</title> and other books published in the <term type="dynasty" ref="/keyword/k000070">Qing dynasty</term>. Architectural historians use this term to describe buildings from the <term type="dynasty" ref="/keyword/k000051">Ming</term> and Qing dynasties.
               </p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000225-2">平板枋為置於<term ref="/keyword/k000115">額枋</term>之上、承接<term ref="/keyword/k000019">斗栱</term>的枋類構件（梁思成 1981，77）。學者通常認為其等同於<term type="dynasty" ref="/keyword/k000074">宋</term>《營造法式》中的<term ref="/keyword/k000218">普拍方</term>。主要見於清工部<title ref="https://tinyurl.com/bd6byucb">《工程做法》</title>，也見用於《圓明園內工則例》、《地宮作法》和《揚州畫舫錄》等<term type="dynasty" ref="/keyword/k000070">清代</term>官式建築和城市營造技術的記載。當代建築史學者用此類術語描述清代建築物，有時候也會用平板枋來描述<term type="dynasty" ref="/keyword/k000051">明代</term>建築物。</p>
            </note>
            <note type="Related concepts">
               <p><term ref="/keyword/k000218">普拍方 pǔpāifāng</term></p>
               <p><term ref="/keyword/k000038">闌額 lán'é</term></p>
               <p><term ref="/keyword/k000115">額枋 é'fāng</term></p>
            </note>
